3. Application Workflow
Phase 1: User Registration

Create an account using a phone number

Receive SMS verification code

Create a password

Phase 2: Form Completion

The user fills out their complete profile.

After submission:

The request is stored in the database

Automatically analyzed

Displayed to the company in the dashboard

Phase 3: Request Analysis

The application sorts requests by:

Region

Purchasing power

Type of housing required

Bank financing availability

This helps the company decide:

üëâ Where to build
üëâ What to build
üëâ How many units to build

4. Detailed Form for Housing Applicants
Section 1: Personal Identity

First and last name

Date of birth

National ID number

Phone number

Email address

Section 2: Family Status

Marital status

Number of children

Supports another family?

Section 3: Employment Status

Profession

Contract type (permanent / temporary / self-employed)

Employer

Duration of current employment

Net monthly income

Section 4: Financial Status

Total household income

Monthly obligations

Current loans

Monthly saving capacity

Section 5: Bank Financing

Bank name

Active bank account?

Previously applied for a loan?

Preliminary approval?

Eligible for subsidized housing programs?

Section 6: Current Housing Situation

Living with family?

Renting?

Owns a home?

Living in informal housing?

Living in a rural area?

Section 7: Desired Housing Characteristics

Governorate

District

Proximity to workplace

Proximity to schools

Housing type:

Individual housing

Collective housing (apartment)

Required area

Number of rooms

Maximum budget

Acceptable delivery time

5. Application Scoring System

Each application receives points based on:

Financial stability

Family size

Lack of home ownership

Bank financing eligibility

Result:

üîπ Priority applicants are highlighted
üîπ Construction decisions become easier

6. Real Estate Projects Interface

The application includes an interactive map.

Each project displays:

Project location

Number of units

Housing type

Expected price

Completion percentage

Delivery date

Project Categories

Projects under study (not started yet)

Projects under construction:

90 days

180 days

1 year

Ready-for-sale projects

7. Investor Interface

A dedicated interface including:

Investment project profile

Location study

Land cost

Construction cost

Total cost

Number of units

Expected selling price

Project duration

Expected return

Risk level

Investor Functions

Download project study (PDF)

Request participation

Specify investment amount

Track project progress

View completion percentage

Monitor profits

8. Back Office (Admin Dashboard)
Request Management

Classification by governorate

Classification by income

Classification by bank

Identify real demand in each area

Project Management

Add projects

Set map location

Enter costs

Enter construction duration

Set expected price

Investor Management

Track contributions

Calculate profits

Distribute returns

Generate financial reports

9. Technical Requirements

The application must:

Work on mobile and web

Load quickly

Support Arabic and French

Integrate with Google Maps

Send SMS notifications

Send push notifications

10. Security and Data Protection

Password encryption

Personal data protection

No sharing of banking information

Compliance with Tunisian laws

